00:08:41.070 --> 00:08:44.270
here we set the scores
for that particular player

00:08:44.270 --> 00:08:47.570
on a particular leader board.

00:08:47.570 --> 00:08:49.890
You've got your QA
person who has managed

00:08:49.890 --> 00:08:53.770
to get some amazing
high score, possibly

00:08:53.770 --> 00:08:55.460
by finding a bug in your game.

00:08:55.460 --> 00:08:59.504
And you want to make sure
they can reset and try again.

00:08:59.504 --> 00:09:00.920
See if they can
reproduce the bug.

00:09:00.920 --> 00:09:05.280
They can call this reset
call to reset that score.

00:09:05.280 --> 00:09:09.170
We also have a similar call
to reset an achievement.

00:09:09.170 --> 00:09:12.280
This is especially
helpful for testing.

00:09:12.280 --> 00:09:15.130
You've got your
QA person that is

00:09:15.130 --> 00:09:16.460
trying to earn an achievement.

00:09:16.460 --> 00:09:18.070
They do it once.

00:09:18.070 --> 00:09:20.080
If they want to try
and do it again,

00:09:20.080 --> 00:09:23.810
the easiest way would--
again, from within your app--

00:09:23.810 --> 00:09:25.900
set up something to
make this call directly.

00:09:25.900 --> 00:09:29.960
And we also have another method
to reset all achievements.

00:09:29.960 --> 00:09:32.230
Again, very useful for testing.

00:09:32.230 --> 00:09:34.610
Remember again that
these calls only

00:09:34.610 --> 00:09:39.530
